	<text>
		<body>
			<div type="transcription">
				<div type="original" xml:lang="cs">
					<pb facs="EHRI-ET-JMP004_01.jpg" n="1"/>
					<p>Dne <date when="1944-10-20">20.10.1944</date> byl v <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0">Osvětímě</placeName> v lágru E sestaven <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">pracovní</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">transport</term>. Při kontrolní prohlídce byli pro tělesnou slabost vyšetřujícím <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287" type="subject">lékařem</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term> vyňati: <persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev">Zeev Scheck</persName>, <persName ref="#https://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/91551-egon-haas/">Egon Haas</persName> a <persName
							ref="#ehri_et_simonsohn_berthold">Bertl Simonsohn</persName>, protože vypadali velmi hubeně. Byli utišováni, že budou posláni jako <q><foreign xml:lang="de"><distinct type="camp_language">Stubendienst</distinct></foreign></q> na nějaký čas do <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">lágru</term>, aby se zotavili a pak že budou posláni na <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">práci</term>. Přes to tušili, oč jde a hlavně <persName
							ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev">Zeev</persName> snažil se dostat <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">transportu</term> tím, že ukazoval svaly a ujišťoval, že je na těžkou práci zvyklý, že jenom tak hubeně vypadá a že je úplně zdráv.
							<persName ref="#https://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/91551-egon-haas/">Egon Haas</persName> a <persName ref="#ehri_et_simonsohn_berthold">Bertl Simonsohn</persName> se k tomu přidali. Přes to nepochodili a jenom proto, že scházeli lidé do <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">transportu</term>, byli na konec k <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">transportu</term> připojení.</p>
					<p>Je zajímavé, že z tohoto <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">transportu</term> zůstali celkem 4 lidé na živu, mezi nimi <persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev">Zeev</persName> a <persName ref="#ehri_et_simonsohn_berthold"
							>Bertl</persName>.</p>
					<p>Protokol přijala: Vlastnoruční podpis svědka:</p>
					<p>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_kratkova_marta">Marta Kratková</persName>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_nasch_erich">Dr. Nasch</persName>
					</p>
					<p>Za <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-657" type="subject">dokumentační akci</term>:</p>
					<p>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev">Zeev Scheck</persName>
					</p>
					<p>Za archiv:</p>
					<p>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_schmiedt_alexander">Alex. Schmiedt</persName>
					</p>
				</div>
				<div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
					<pb facs="EHRI-ET-JMP004_01.jpg" n="1"/>
					<p>On <date when="1944-10-20">20.10.1944</date> a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">labor</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">transport</term> was put together in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0">Auschwitz</placeName> in camp E. During the medical check-up, the examining <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287" type="subject">doctor</term>removed the following people due to physical weakness: <persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev">Zeev Scheck</persName>, <persName
							ref="https://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/91551-egon-haas/">Egon Haas</persName>, and <persName ref="#ehri_et_simonsohn_berthold">Bertl Simonsohn</persName>, because they looked very thin. They were assured that they would be sent as <q><foreign xml:lang="de"
									><distinct type="camp_language">Stubendienst</distinct></foreign></q> to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term> for a short time so that they could get better and then be sent to <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term>. But they knew what was going on and <persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev">Zeev</persName> especially tried to get onto the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">transport</term> by showing his muscles and vowing that he was used to hard work, that he only appeared thin, but that he was completely healthy. <persName
							ref="https://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/91551-egon-haas/">Egon Haas</persName> and <persName ref="#ehri_et_simonsohn_berthold">Bertl Simonsohn</persName> joined him. They weren’t successful, but were added to the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">transport</term> in the end only because some people were missing.</p>
					<p>It’s interesting that only 4 people survived this <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">transport</term>, and <persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev">Zeev</persName> and <persName ref="#ehri_et_simonsohn_berthold">Bertl</persName> are
						among them.</p>
					<p>Statement was accepted by: <space> </space>Signature of the witness:</p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_kratkova_marta">Marta Kratková</persName>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_nasch_erich">Dr.Nasch</persName></p>
					<p>On behalf of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-657" type="subject">Documentation campaign</term>:</p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev">Zeev Scheck</persName></p>
					<p>On behalf of the archive:</p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_schmiedt_alexander">Alex. Schmiedt</persName></p>
				</div>
